cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it discusses a high-level language for programming protocol-independent packet processors that work in conjunction with SDN control protocols like OpenFlow. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it discusses the reconfigurability of switches in the field, which is a security concern. Additionally, it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category as it discusses the need for switches to be protocol-independent and target-independent. It may also belong to the Architecture (cs.AR) category as it discusses the evolution of OpenFlow and proposes a new approach. Finally, it may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category as it introduces a new high-level language for programming packet processors.
